A law graduate of Benue State University, Makurdi, Adzua Defence was Tuesday night shot dead by suspected cult members in the capital city. The incident, according to sources occurred at Gyado villa street in Makurdi. It was gathered that the late law graduate was, into modelling in Lagos and had come home since Christmas break and had planned to travel back to Lagos yesterday (Wednesday) when he was shot in the head. He was said to have been rushed to the State University Teaching Hospital, Makurdi where he died. Man allegedly kills mother in Benue Supreme Court verdict: We will not tolerate any breach of… Benue govt converts institutions to Polytechnic No open grazing in Benue State ―Ortom’s CPS ALSO READ: Establish correctional homes to tackle juvenile delinquency in Oyo, Assembly charges Ministry The killing, according to an eyewitness who did not want to be mentioned almost lead to a protest before policemen brought the situation under control. Confirming the incident, the Police Public Relations Officer, Catherine Anene, a Deputy Superintendent of Police said that the planned protest by some students was stopped by policemen “I can confirm the report, though we are still waiting for more details from the station. But we (police) had to move around the area yesterday (Tuesday) to stop the planned protest,” Anene said. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE.